{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|木|射|c1=s|c2=p|t1=wood; wooden structure|ls=psc}}; also {{Han compound|木|射|t2=[[archery]]|ls=ic|nocap=yes}}, as it originally referred to an early type of architecture for both the practice and the ceremony of archery: an open-space hall built on raised ground, without internal division into rooms ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1923}}; {{zh-ref|Yang, 1965}}). In bronze script, the alternative form {{zh-m|*𫷺}} (i.e. {{lang|zh|⿸广射}}) can be seen.

